        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1737229198" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1552969185214406979">This was a decent read, it is just simply put not my genre. I&apos;m going to ignore the latter and give it a 4, otherwise, a 3 on this laundry room find.<br/><br/>The characters are compelling and well developed. I didn&apos;t find it quite so mysterious as a classic mystery book and I understand it&apos;s suppose to be a medieval mystery of sorts. The periodness was reasonably done. I would say the authors ability to describe a setting was excellent. <br/><br/>Again, just not my genre that I will be actively seeking out the oth</span>
  <span id="freeText1552969185214406979" style="display:none">This was a decent read, it is just simply put not my genre. I'm going to ignore the latter and give it a 4, otherwise, a 3 on this laundry room find.<br /><br />The characters are compelling and well developed. I didn't find it quite so mysterious as a classic mystery book and I understand it's suppose to be a medieval mystery of sorts. The periodness was reasonably done. I would say the authors ability to describe a setting was excellent. <br /><br />Again, just not my genre that I will be actively seeking out the others in the series. I mean, if they end up in my Laundry Room, maybe, but we'll see. </span>
